---
// Ubuntu Budgie Welcome — Getting Started, macOS-style
---
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8" />
  <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
  <title>Ubuntu Budgie Welcome — Getting Started</title>
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=DM+Sans:wght@300;400;500;600&display=swap" rel="stylesheet" />
  <style>
    *, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }

    :root {
      --bg:            #e8e8e8;
      --win-bg:        #ffffff;
      --bar-bg:        #f5f5f5;
      --bar-border:    #e0e0e0;
      --panel-bg:      #f9f9f9;
      --panel-border:  #ebebeb;
      --text-primary:  #1a1a1a;
      --text-secondary:#6b6b6b;
      --text-tertiary: #9b9b9b;
      --accent:        #2563eb;
      --accent-light:  #dbeafe;
      --hover-bg:      #efefef;
      --card-border:   #e8e8e8;
      --green:         #16a34a;
      --green-light:   #dcfce7;
      --amber-light:   #fef3c7;
      --amber:         #d97706;
      --red-light:     #fee2e2;
      --red:           #dc2626;
      --shadow-sm:     0 1px 3px rgba(0,0,0,.06), 0 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,.04);
      --shadow-win:    0 20px 60px rgba(0,0,0,.18), 0 8px 24px rgba(0,0,0,.10);
      --radius-sm:     6px;
      --radius-md:     10px;
      --radius-win:    14px;
      --font:          'DM Sans', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, sans-serif;
    }

    html, body {
      height: 100%; overflow: hidden;
      background: var(--bg); font-family: var(--font);
      display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
      padding: 24px;
    }

    /* ── Window ── */
    .window {
      width: 900px; max-width: 100%;
      height: calc(100vh - 48px);
      max-height: 700px; min-height: 480px;
      background: var(--win-bg); border-radius: var(--radius-win);
      box-shadow: var(--shadow-win); overflow: hidden;
      display: flex; flex-direction: column;
      animation: fadeUp .3s ease both;
    }
    @keyframes fadeUp {
      from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(6px); }
      to   { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
    }

    /* ── Title Bar ── */
    .titlebar {
      height: 44px; background: var(--bar-bg);
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--bar-border);
      display: flex; align-items: center;
      padding: 0 16px; gap: 8px;
      flex-shrink: 0; position: relative; user-select: none;
    }
    .back-btn {
      display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 5px;
      background: none; border: none; cursor: pointer;
      color: var(--accent); font-family: var(--font);
      font-size: 13px; font-weight: 500;
      padding: 4px 6px 4px 2px; border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
      transition: background .12s; text-decoration: none; line-height: 1;
    }
    .back-btn:hover { background: rgba(37,99,235,.08); }
    .back-btn svg { width: 16px; height: 16px; }
    .titlebar-label {
      position: absolute; left: 50%; transform: translateX(-50%);
      font-size: 13px; font-weight: 500;
      color: var(--text-secondary); letter-spacing: -.01em; pointer-events: none;
    }

    /* ── Body split: topic list + content ── */
    .body-split {
      flex: 1; display: flex; overflow: hidden; min-height: 0;
    }

    /* ── Topic List (left panel, inside content) ── */
    .topic-list {
      width: 188px; flex-shrink: 0;
      background: var(--panel-bg);
      border-right: 1px solid var(--panel-border);
      display: flex; flex-direction: column;
      padding: 10px 0; overflow-y: auto;
    }
    .topic-list::-webkit-scrollbar { width: 4px; }
    .topic-list::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb { background: #d4d4d4; border-radius: 2px; }

    .topic-section-label {
      font-size: 10px; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: .07em;
      text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--text-tertiary);
      padding: 10px 14px 4px;
    }
    .topic-item {
      display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px;
      padding: 6px 10px; margin: 0 5px;
      border-radius: var(--radius-sm); cursor: pointer;
      background: none; border: none; text-align: left;
      font-family: var(--font); font-size: 13px; color: var(--text-primary);
      transition: background .1s, color .1s; width: calc(100% - 10px);
    }
    .topic-item:hover { background: var(--hover-bg); }
    .topic-item.active { background: var(--accent-light); color: var(--accent); font-weight: 500; }
    .topic-item .t-icon {
      width: 24px; height: 24px; border-radius: 6px; flex-shrink: 0;
      display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
      font-size: 13px;
    }
    .topic-item.active .t-icon { opacity: 1; }

    /* ── Content Panel ── */
    .content-panel {
      flex: 1; display: flex; flex-direction: column; overflow: hidden; min-height: 0;
    }
    .content-scroll {
      flex: 1; overflow-y: auto; min-height: 0; padding: 24px 28px 28px;
    }
    .content-scroll::-webkit-scrollbar { width: 6px; }
    .content-scroll::-webkit-scrollbar-track { background: transparent; }
    .content-scroll::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb { background: #d4d4d4; border-radius: 3px; }
    .content-scroll::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb:hover { background: #aaa; }

    /* ── Topic pages — hidden by default ── */
    .topic-page { display: none; animation: fadeUp .22s ease both; }
    .topic-page.active { display: block; }

    /* ── Typography ── */
    .page-title {
      font-size: 20px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-primary);
      letter-spacing: -.02em; margin-bottom: 5px;
    }
    .page-subtitle {
      font-size: 13px; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.55;
      margin-bottom: 20px; max-width: 520px;
    }
    .section-title {
      font-size: 13.5px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-primary); margin-bottom: 8px;
    }
    .body-text {
      font-size: 13px; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.65;
    }
    .body-text p + p { margin-top: 8px; }
    .body-text a { color: var(--accent); text-decoration: none; }
    .body-text a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
    .body-text strong, .body-text b { color: var(--text-primary); font-weight: 500; }
    .body-text code {
      background: #f0f0f0; border: 1px solid var(--card-border);
      border-radius: 4px; padding: 1px 5px; font-size: 12px; font-family: monospace;
    }
    .body-text ul { padding-left: 18px; }
    .body-text li { margin-bottom: 4px; }

    /* ── Divider ── */
    .divider { height: 1px; background: var(--card-border); margin: 18px 0; }

    /* ── Cat divider ── */
    .cat-divider {
      display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px; margin: 20px 0 12px;
    }
    .cat-label {
      font-size: 10px; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: .07em;
      text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--text-tertiary); white-space: nowrap;
    }
    .cat-line { flex: 1; height: 1px; background: var(--card-border); }

    /* ── Spec cards ── */
    .spec-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 10px; margin: 14px 0; }
    .spec-card {
      background: #fafafa; border: 1px solid var(--card-border);
      border-radius: var(--radius-md); padding: 14px 16px;
    }
    .spec-card-title {
      font-size: 11px; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: .05em;
      text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--text-tertiary); margin-bottom: 8px;
    }
    .spec-row { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: baseline; padding: 3px 0; }
    .spec-row + .spec-row { border-top: 1px solid var(--card-border); }
    .spec-key { font-size: 12px; color: var(--text-secondary); }
    .spec-val { font-size: 12px; color: var(--text-primary); font-weight: 500; }

    /* ── Feature row ── */
    .feature-row {
      display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: 14px;
      padding: 14px 16px; border-radius: var(--radius-md);
      border: 1px solid var(--card-border); background: #fafafa;
      margin-bottom: 8px; transition: box-shadow .15s, transform .1s;
    }
    .feature-row:hover { box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm); transform: translateY(-1px); }
    .feature-icon {
      width: 42px; height: 42px; border-radius: 10px;
      display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
      background: #f0f0f0; flex-shrink: 0; overflow: hidden;
    }
    .feature-icon img { width: 34px; height: 34px; object-fit: contain; }
    .feature-text { flex: 1; min-width: 0; }
    .feature-name { font-size: 13px; font-weight: 500; color: var(--text-primary); margin-bottom: 3px; }
    .feature-desc { font-size: 12.5px; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.6; }
    .feature-desc a { color: var(--accent); text-decoration: none; }
    .feature-desc a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }

    /* ── Action button ── */
    .action-btn {
      display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px;
      padding: 7px 14px; border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
      font-family: var(--font); font-size: 12.5px; font-weight: 500;
      cursor: pointer; border: none; transition: background .12s, transform .1s;
      text-decoration: none; margin-top: 8px;
    }
    .action-btn:active { transform: scale(.98); }
    .action-btn.primary   { background: var(--accent); color: #fff; }
    .action-btn.primary:hover { background: #1d4ed8; }
    .action-btn.success   { background: #16a34a; color: #fff; }
    .action-btn.success:hover { background: #15803d; }
    .action-btn.neutral   { background: #3f3f3f; color: #fff; }
    .action-btn.neutral:hover { background: #1a1a1a; }
    .action-btn.danger    { background: var(--red); color: #fff; }
    .action-btn.danger:hover { background: #b91c1c; }
    .action-btn svg, .action-btn img { width: 15px; height: 15px; }

    /* ── Alert boxes ── */
    .alert {
      border-radius: var(--radius-sm); padding: 11px 14px;
      font-size: 12.5px; line-height: 1.55; margin: 12px 0;
    }
    .alert.info    { background: #eff6ff; border: 1px solid #bfdbfe; color: #1e40af; }
    .alert.warn    { background: #fffbeb; border: 1px solid #fcd34d; color: #92400e; }
    .alert.danger  { background: var(--red-light); border: 1px solid #fca5a5; color: #991b1b; }
    .alert.success { background: var(--green-light); border: 1px solid #86efac; color: #14532d; }
    .alert strong  { font-weight: 600; }

    /* ── Tab bar ── */
    .tab-bar { display: flex; gap: 4px; margin-bottom: 14px; }
    .tab-btn {
      padding: 5px 14px; border-radius: 20px; border: 1px solid var(--card-border);
      font-family: var(--font); font-size: 12.5px; font-weight: 500;
      cursor: pointer; background: #fafafa; color: var(--text-secondary);
      transition: background .12s, color .12s, border-color .12s;
    }
    .tab-btn.active { background: var(--accent); color: #fff; border-color: var(--accent); }
    .tab-btn:hover:not(.active) { background: var(--hover-bg); color: var(--text-primary); }
    .tab-content { display: none; }
    .tab-content.active { display: block; animation: fadeUp .18s ease both; }

    /* ── Browser grid ── */
    .browser-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 10px; }
    .browser-card {
      background: #fafafa; border: 1px solid var(--card-border);
      border-radius: var(--radius-md); padding: 14px 16px;
      display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 8px;
    }
    .browser-header { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px; }
    .browser-icon { width: 36px; height: 36px; object-fit: contain; }
    .browser-name { font-size: 13.5px; font-weight: 500; color: var(--text-primary); }
    .browser-desc { font-size: 12px; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.55; }
    .browser-actions { display: flex; gap: 6px; flex-wrap: wrap; }

    /* ── Input method grid ── */
    .input-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 8px; margin: 10px 0; }
    .input-card {
      background: #fafafa; border: 1px solid var(--card-border);
      border-radius: var(--radius-md); padding: 12px;
      text-align: center;
    }
    .input-card-title { font-size: 13px; font-weight: 500; margin-bottom: 8px; color: var(--text-primary); }

    /* ── Checkbox ── */
    .check-label {
      display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px;
      font-size: 13px; color: var(--text-secondary);
      cursor: pointer; margin: 10px 0;
    }
    .check-label input { width: 15px; height: 15px; accent-color: var(--accent); cursor: pointer; }

    /* ── Footer ── */
    .win-footer {
      display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between;
      padding: 9px 24px; border-top: 1px solid var(--card-border);
      background: var(--bar-bg); flex-shrink: 0;
    }
    .discourse-link {
      display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 7px; text-decoration: none;
      font-size: 12px; color: var(--text-secondary);
    }
    .discourse-link img { height: 18px; }
    .social-links { display: flex; gap: 4px; }
    .social-link {
      width: 28px; height: 28px; border-radius: 6px;
      display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
      color: var(--text-tertiary); text-decoration: none;
      transition: background .12s, color .12s;
      border: none; background: transparent; cursor: pointer;
    }
    .social-link:hover { background: var(--hover-bg); color: var(--text-primary); }
    .social-link svg { width: 14px; height: 14px; }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="window">

  <!-- Title Bar -->
  <div class="titlebar">
    <a href="index" class="back-btn">
      <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2.2" stroke="currentColor">
        <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M15.75 19.5 8.25 12l7.5-7.5"/>
      </svg>
      Back
    </a>
    <span class="titlebar-label">Getting Started</span>
  </div>

  <div class="body-split">

    <!-- ── Topic List ── -->
    <nav class="topic-list" id="topicList">
      <span class="topic-section-label">Installation</span>
      <button class="topic-item active" data-topic="sysreq">
        <span class="t-icon">💻</span> System Requirements
      </button>
      <button class="topic-item" data-topic="prepare">
        <span class="t-icon">📋</span> Preparing to Install
      </button>
      <button class="topic-item" data-topic="dualboot">
        <span class="t-icon">⚙️</span> Dual Booting
      </button>

      <span class="topic-section-label">Setup</span>
      <button class="topic-item" data-topic="updates">
        <span class="t-icon">🔄</span> Updates &amp; Extras
      </button>
      <button class="topic-item" data-topic="drivers">
        <span class="t-icon">🖥️</span> Drivers
      </button>
      <button class="topic-item" data-topic="languageInput">
        <span class="t-icon">🌐</span> Language &amp; Input
      </button>

      <span class="topic-section-label">Discover</span>
      <button class="topic-item" data-topic="tasks">
        <span class="t-icon">📦</span> Optional Tasks
      </button>
      <button class="topic-item" data-topic="browsers">
        <span class="t-icon">🌍</span> Browsers
      </button>
    </nav>

    <!-- ── Content Panel ── -->
    <div class="content-panel">
      <div class="content-scroll">

        <!-- ══ System Requirements ══ -->
        <div class="topic-page active" id="page-sysreq">
          <div class="page-title">System Requirements</div>
          <div class="page-subtitle">Ubuntu Budgie works well on both high-end and older computers, optimised to be functional while light on system resources.</div>

          <div class="spec-grid">
            <div class="spec-card">
              <div class="spec-card-title">Minimum — PC</div>
              <div class="spec-row"><span class="spec-key">CPU</span><span class="spec-val">Intel i3 (≈ 2013)</span></div>
              <div class="spec-row"><span class="spec-key">RAM</span><span class="spec-val">2 GB</span></div>
              <div class="spec-row"><span class="spec-key">Storage</span><span class="spec-val">32 GB</span></div>
            </div>
            <div class="spec-card">
              <div class="spec-card-title">Recommended — PC</div>
              <div class="spec-row"><span class="spec-key">CPU</span><span class="spec-val">Intel i5 (≈ 2017)</span></div>
              <div class="spec-row"><span class="spec-key">RAM</span><span class="spec-val">4 GB</span></div>
              <div class="spec-row"><span class="spec-key">Storage</span><span class="spec-val">60 GB</span></div>
            </div>
            <div class="spec-card">
              <div class="spec-card-title">Minimum — Raspberry Pi</div>
              <div class="spec-row"><span class="spec-key">Model</span><span class="spec-val">Pi 4B</span></div>
              <div class="spec-row"><span class="spec-key">RAM</span><span class="spec-val">2 GB</span></div>
              <div class="spec-row"><span class="spec-key">SD Card</span><span class="spec-val">32 GB</span></div>
            </div>
            <div class="spec-card">
              <div class="spec-card-title">Recommended — Raspberry Pi</div>
              <div class="spec-row"><span class="spec-key">Model</span><span class="spec-val">Pi 4B</span></div>
              <div class="spec-row"><span class="spec-key">RAM</span><span class="spec-val">4 GB</span></div>
              <div class="spec-row"><span class="spec-key">SSD</span><span class="spec-val">60 GB</span></div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="body-text">
            <p>The operating system will run much more efficiently if your computer meets or surpasses the recommended requirements.</p>
          </div>
          <button class="action-btn neutral" data-goto="prepare">
            Next: Preparing to Install →
          </button>
        </div>

        <!-- ══ Preparing to Install ══ -->
        <div class="topic-page" id="page-prepare">
          <div class="page-title">Preparing to Install</div>
          <div class="page-subtitle">Ubuntu Budgie is relatively simple to set up, whether replacing your existing OS or installing alongside it.</div>

          <div class="section-title">For the best results</div>
          <div class="body-text">
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Back up</strong> any important data to another storage device.</li>
              <li>Connect to the internet to install all available updates during installation.</li>
              <li>Plug in your device if it is running on battery power.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="divider"></div>

          <div class="feature-row">
            <div class="feature-icon"><img src="img/applications/ubiquity.png" alt="Installer" /></div>
            <div class="feature-text">
              <div class="feature-name">Live Session</div>
              <div class="feature-desc">The live session you are currently in is a good opportunity to test Ubuntu Budgie without modifying your computer — test that all your peripherals work before committing to installation. Once ready, double click the installation icon on the desktop.</div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="cat-divider"><span class="cat-label">UEFI &amp; Secure Boot</span><div class="cat-line"></div></div>
          <div class="body-text">
            <p>If you have a modern PC using UEFI, you may need to disable <strong>Secure Boot</strong> (or enable <strong>Unlock Bootloader</strong>) prior to installation, particularly if an OS was pre-installed.</p>
            <p>When dual booting, boot your system in the correct mode and use the <strong>64-bit image</strong> — you cannot boot an OS installed in BIOS mode after installing a UEFI-enabled OS, or vice versa.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="alert info" id="boot-mode-alert">
            Your system is currently running in <strong><span id="boot-mode">UEFI</span> mode</strong>.
          </div>

          <div class="cat-divider"><span class="cat-label">Swap</span><div class="cat-line"></div></div>
          <div class="body-text">
            <p>When running low on RAM, the OS will start swapping to disk (known as a "paging file" in Windows). A swap file is created automatically based on the size of your RAM — a separate swap partition is no longer required.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- ══ Dual Booting ══ -->
        <div class="topic-page" id="page-dualboot">
          <div class="page-title">Dual Booting</div>
          <div class="page-subtitle">Install Ubuntu Budgie alongside your existing OS by shrinking partitions to share your hard disk.</div>

          <div class="section-title">Before you begin</div>
          <div class="body-text">
            <ul>
              <li>Ensure there is enough free space — 10 GB minimum is recommended.</li>
              <li><strong>Back up</strong> important data to another drive.</li>
              <li>Defragment the hard drive (Windows only).</li>
              <li>Ensure Windows has been cleanly shut down — not hibernated.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="check-label">
            <input type="checkbox" id="showDualBootWin" />
            <label for="showDualBootWin">I'm dual booting with Microsoft Windows</label>
          </div>

          <div class="cat-divider"><span class="cat-label">Choose your approach</span><div class="cat-line"></div></div>

          <div class="tab-bar">
            <button class="tab-btn active" data-group="dualboot" data-tab="simple">Simple</button>
            <button class="tab-btn" data-group="dualboot" data-tab="advanced">Advanced</button>
            <button class="tab-btn" data-group="dualboot" data-tab="windows">Safest (Windows)</button>
          </div>

          <div class="tab-content active" id="dualboot-simple">
            <div class="section-title">Use the installer</div>
            <div class="body-text">
              <p>The installer scans your disks for existing operating systems and provides a choice of what you'd like to do — the simplest and most guided approach.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="alert danger">
              <strong>Do not interrupt or power off during a resize operation.</strong> Data loss or partition table corruption could occur. The installer may show a spinner for a long time depending on disk size.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="tab-content" id="dualboot-advanced">
            <div class="feature-row" style="margin-bottom:10px;">
              <div class="feature-icon"><img src="img/applications/gparted.png" alt="GParted" /></div>
              <div class="feature-text">
                <div class="feature-name">GParted</div>
                <div class="feature-desc">Available during the live session under <strong>System Tools</strong>. Provides complete flexibility over your partitions — primarily for power users who know their preferred disk layout. Makes changes before installation.</div>
                <button class="action-btn neutral" data-cmd="gparted">Open GParted</button>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="section-title">Common mount points</div>
            <div class="body-text">
              <ul>
                <li><code>/</code> — Base for Ubuntu Budgie</li>
                <li><code>/home</code> — Your personal files and folders</li>
                <li><code>/boot</code> — Bootloader and kernels</li>
                <li><code>/tmp</code> — Temporary files</li>
                <li><code>/usr</code> — Applications, libraries and documentation</li>
                <li><code>/var</code> — Variable data (system logs, etc.)</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="tab-content" id="dualboot-windows">
            <div class="body-text">
              <p>The safest method when dual booting with Windows is to shrink the partition from within Windows <strong>before</strong> starting the installer:</p>
              <ul style="margin-top:8px;">
                <li>Open <strong>Disk Management</strong> in Windows.</li>
                <li>Right-click the Windows partition → <strong>Shrink Volume</strong>.</li>
                <li>Leave the resulting free space unallocated — the installer will use it.</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="alert info">After installation, run <code>chkdsk /f</code> from the Windows command prompt to check the NTFS file system for errors.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- ══ Updates & Extras ══ -->
        <div class="topic-page" id="page-updates">
          <div class="page-title">Updates &amp; Extras</div>
          <div class="page-subtitle">Keep Ubuntu Budgie current and unlock support for popular media formats.</div>

          <div class="alert warn" id="offline-warn">
            An internet connection is required to download and install updates.
          </div>

          <div class="feature-row">
            <div class="feature-icon"><img src="img/applications/system-software-update.png" alt="Software Updater" /></div>
            <div class="feature-text">
              <div class="feature-name">Software Updater</div>
              <div class="feature-desc">Ubuntu Budgie periodically checks for new software and security updates. If you've just installed, check for updates now. Software Updater can also be found later under <strong>System Tools</strong>.</div>
              <button class="action-btn primary" data-cmd="update">Check for Updates</button>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="feature-row">
            <div class="feature-icon"><img src="img/applications/codecs.png" alt="Restricted Extras" /></div>
            <div class="feature-text">
              <div class="feature-name">Restricted Extras</div>
              <div class="feature-desc">Install support for popular non-free media formats including DVD, MP3, QuickTime, and Windows Media formats. Patent and copyright laws vary by country — obtain legal advice if unsure.</div>
              <div style="display:flex;gap:8px;flex-wrap:wrap;">
                <button class="action-btn success" id="restricted-extras-install" data-cmd="install?restricted-extras">Install</button>
                <button class="action-btn danger" id="restricted-extras-remove" data-cmd="remove?restricted-extras">Remove</button>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- ══ Drivers ══ -->
        <div class="topic-page" id="page-drivers">
          <div class="page-title">Drivers</div>
          <div class="page-subtitle">Some hardware components require proprietary drivers to function correctly, particularly Bluetooth and Wi-Fi.</div>

          <div class="alert warn">An internet connection is required to download and install drivers.</div>

          <div class="feature-row">
            <div class="feature-icon"><img src="img/applications/additional-drivers.png" alt="Additional Drivers" /></div>
            <div class="feature-text">
              <div class="feature-name">Additional Drivers</div>
              <div class="feature-desc">Ubuntu Budgie can automatically detect hardware that needs proprietary drivers. Additional Drivers can also be found later under <strong>System Tools</strong>.</div>
              <button class="action-btn neutral" data-cmd="drivers">Open Additional Drivers</button>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="cat-divider"><span class="cat-label">Graphics</span><div class="cat-line"></div></div>

          <div class="alert success graphics-intel" style="display:none;">
            <strong>Intel graphics detected.</strong> Intel's drivers are open source and maintained in the kernel — you're already good to go.
          </div>
          <div class="alert info graphics-nvidia" style="display:none;">
            <strong>NVIDIA graphics detected.</strong> NVIDIA drivers can boost performance for 3D applications and games and improve power management.
          </div>
          <div class="alert success graphics-amd" style="display:none;">
            <strong>AMD graphics detected.</strong> AMD's proprietary drivers are no longer supported on Ubuntu — the open source drivers you're using deliver the most stable performance.
          </div>

          <div class="body-text" id="graphics-proprietary">
            <p>Proprietary drivers come directly from the manufacturer and can <strong>significantly improve graphics performance</strong>. Users may wish to install these to:</p>
            <ul style="margin-top:8px;">
              <li>Run 3D applications and games.</li>
              <li>Improve power management and reduce overheating.</li>
              <li>Better support for high resolutions and multiple monitors.</li>
            </ul>
            <p style="margin-top:8px;">However proprietary drivers are not open source — issues such as broken drivers after upgrades or graphical glitches are possible.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="cat-divider"><span class="cat-label">Wireless &amp; Bluetooth</span><div class="cat-line"></div></div>
          <div class="body-text">
            <p>If Additional Drivers finds nothing and your device still doesn't work, the manufacturer may not have provided source code or sufficient documentation for a driver. Some manufacturers provide closed-source drivers directly.</p>
            <p><a href="community" class="text-link">Ask the community</a> if you need assistance, or <a data-cmd="link?https://help.ubuntu.com/community/WifiDocs/WirelessTroubleShootingGuide/Drivers" class="text-link" style="cursor:pointer;">read the wireless troubleshooting guide</a>.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

